pull.title: Fix osslsigncode compile issue in gitian-build
pull.body:
Install libssl1.0-dev that is compatible with osslsigncode.

Fixes #13762 

Verifed that this gitian descriptor file can sign 0.16.2rc2.

events.body:
utACK
But please add a comment that this is a workaround that can be removed once `osslsigncode` supports the new API. We've had a case recently where we didn't know why a certain specific version of a lib was enforced anymore.

events.message: Fix osslsigncode compile issue in gitian-build

events.body:
@MarcoFalke @laanwj just as a heads up for the codesigner, compiling osslsigncode with curl (needed for  detached-sig-create.sh) creates an in compatibility between curl which requires libssl-dev and libssl1.0-dev. Therefore that compilation of osslsigncode needs to be performed on ubuntu 16.04.
I'm still not sure why the gitianbuild compiles osslsigncode without curl, as this requires two seperate compiles still.

issue.title: Fix osslsigncode compile issue in gitian-build
issue.body: This is a backport of https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/13782 which allows us to build `osslcodesign` for verifying detached pkcs7 signatures of Windows binaries.

issue.title: Revert "Merge bitcoin#13782: Fix osslsigncode compile issue in gitian-build"
issue.body: We use osslsigncode 2.0 already due to dashpay#3258 so this commit reverts backport of bitcoin#13782 (https://github.com/dashpay/dash/commit/619f7fb862c196b22e4b222b5bc2ff1f56411c12)
